      <ul><br><br>
        <p class="MB_Heading">Skills: Trades</p>
        <ul>
          <p class="MB_SubHead">Mastering Brewing in 2-3 hours in Thurgadin by Slithher Poopypantz</p>
          <ul>
            <p class="MB_Body"> 
                
    <P>I noticed that a lot of the guides to getting started in Brewing were
      made pre-Velious. I also noticed a lot of the items to practice making
      required various components spread throughout the world. Since I'm fairly
      lazy it just didn't interest me much to try and buy foraged items all day
      long in EC. So I made a guide to get you from 1 to 248 if you so desire,
      all within the comfy confines of Thurgadin. </P>
    
    <P>As you enter the zone you will see The Broken Glacier. In there you will
      find the ingredients for brewing from Tobart Dirkins. Pick up the needed
      ingredients, and take a left out and follow the path until you come to the
      entrance to the Thurg mines. Hang a sharp right and you'll come to an open
      area with merchant. On your left is the Entrance to the Velium Keg. </P>
    
    <P>Drop on in to use their brew barrel and purchase casks from most of the
      bar staff. Some of them sell the ingredients but it's usually items
      leftover from players that were sold to the merchants so their quantities
      are limited. The only other thing you will need is water that can be
      picked up at Morodin's Meats on the way to the Keg. Here's the path I took
      and it can get you to over 200 and up to 248 if you so desire. </P>
    
    <P>Try your best to use some int/wis gear and get yourself a buff from an
      enchanter if at all possible. It really does make a huge difference. All
      ingredients are 1 per type except where noted. </P>
    <TABLE BORDER="1" cellspacing="0">
      <TR align="middle">
        <TD>SKILL LEVEL</TD>
        <TD>INGREDIENTS</TD>
        <TD>CONTAINER </TD>
        <TD> FINISHED PRODUCT </TD>
      </TR>
      <TR align="middle">
        <TD>1 to 41</TD>
        <TD> Yeast, hops, malt</TD>
        <TD> Cask</TD>
        <TD>Mead</TD>
      </TR>
      <TR align="middle">
        <TD> 42 to 68</TD>
        <TD> Barley, malt, water</TD>
        <TD> Cask</TD>
        <TD>Ale</TD>
      </TR>
      <TR align="middle">
        <TD> 69 to 135</TD>
        <TD>Barley, hops, yeast, malt </TD>
        <TD> Cask</TD>
        <TD>Ol' Tijim's Fierce Brew</TD>
      </TR>
      <TR align="middle">
        <TD> 136 to 248 </TD>
        <TD>3 malts, yeast, 2 waters, 2 short beers</TD>
        <TD>Cask</TD>
        <TD>Minotaur Hero's Brew </TD>
      </TR>
    </TABLE>
    
    <P>It took me about 2 hours to hit master level with limited int gear and
      enlightenment buff or two. </P>
    
    <P>So I hope you enjoy your path on becoming a brewmeister. </P>
    
    <P>Slithher Poopypantz 53 Disciple Stasis Prexus Jersey@prexus.com   </P>
          </ul>
        </ul>
